      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ALZURRI (7) was ridden quietly then made some inroads to finish 2.25 lengths away over 1625m at this track a week ago. Tackles a longer journey this time and it looks to suit. Peaks and gets in light with the 2kg claim. Hard to beat. PROUD MISS (4) had been threatening to win in stronger Maidens before flopping on the Gold Cast poly. Forget that and back home she has winning claims. PELLINOR (6) was poor here last time and the blinkers come off. Showed enough this distance range at the Sunshine Coast prior in a CL1 to suggest he can get into the finish. RED VEGAS (8) has been plainer her last couple but this is easier and she maps well. Has a handy 3kg claim and is in the mix. JAMCART (3) may be the best of the remainder.",
